## 9. Production Readiness Score

| Dimension | Score | Reasoning |
|---|---|---|
| **Design Quality** | 6/10 | Domain model is sound; module structure is good; but lacks concrete schema, API contracts, and service boundary definitions |
| **Scalability** | 5/10 | Scaling strategy is noted at a high level but critical enablers (connection pooling, seat locking, index strategy, worker separation) are absent |
| **Security** | 5/10 | Baseline measures listed (JWT, HMAC webhooks) but MFA, token revocation, RLS, CORS, and file validation are missing |
| **Maintainability** | 6/10 | Modular monolith with NestJS is maintainable; Prisma is a good ORM choice; missing CI/CD, observability, and migration strategy hurt this score |

**Overall: 5.5 / 10**

> [!NOTE]
> This score reflects the document's readiness as a technical specification, not the quality of the idea or the team. The product vision is clear and well-scoped. The document needs one more engineering pass to be a true technical blueprint before development begins.

