## 10. Required Questions for the Product Owner

---

**PROMPT 1 — Seat Overbooking:**
> "When a category reaches its player limit (e.g., U10 has 50 seats), and two players submit payment simultaneously — one payment succeeds and one fails — which player gets the seat? Describe the exact business rule: should the system reserve a seat at registration creation, or only after payment confirmation? What happens to the player who paid but doesn't get a seat?"

---

**PROMPT 2 — Refund Policy:**
> "Describe the complete refund lifecycle for each scenario: (a) a player withdraws before payment, (b) a player withdraws after payment but before the registration deadline, (c) a player withdraws after the registration deadline, (d) an organiser cancels a tournament after players have paid, (e) a tournament is cancelled by the admin due to a policy violation. For each case: who initiates the refund, what is the timeline, and what percentage is returned?"

---

**PROMPT 3 — Player Identity:**
> "Is a 'Player' always the same person as the logged-in user, or can a parent register a child (who has no account)? If a parent can register a child, how is the child's identity associated with their FIDE ID or national chess federation ID? What prevents a parent from submitting a false date of birth to enter an underage category?"

---

**PROMPT 4 — Organiser Verification:**
> "What is the organiser verification process? Can any person sign up as an organiser and create tournaments immediately, or is there a manual verification step? What documents are required (e.g., FIDE affiliation, identity proof, academy registration certificate)? Who performs this verification — the Super Admin manually, or an automated check?"

---

**PROMPT 5 — Payment Gateway & Commission:**
> "Is Razorpay the confirmed payment gateway, or are alternatives under consideration (e.g., PayU, Cashfree, Stripe for international)? How does the platform's commission model work technically: does the platform collect the full payment and transfer a net amount to the organiser (collect-then-disburse model), or does the gateway split payment at source (Razorpay Route / PayU Smart Collect)? This decision has major regulatory (GST, TDS) and technical implications."

---

**PROMPT 6 — Multi-Currency & International Players:**
> "Will the platform support non-Indian players registering for tournaments? If yes, will fees be charged in INR only, or also in foreign currencies? Are cross-border payment regulations and RBI guidelines considered? This affects payment gateway selection and KYC requirements."

---

**PROMPT 7 — WhatsApp Notification Compliance:**
> "WhatsApp Business API requires pre-approved message templates and a Meta Business account with phone number verification. Has this process been initiated? If WhatsApp notifications are not available at launch, what is the fallback — email only, or SMS via a provider like Twilio/MSG91? Are players required to opt-in to WhatsApp notifications?"

---

**PROMPT 8 — Tournament Data Ownership:**
> "If an organiser's account is suspended or deleted, what happens to their tournaments and the player registrations under those tournaments? Players have paid fees and expect to participate — who is responsible for notifying them and processing refunds? Does the platform retain tournament data permanently, or is there a data retention policy?"

---

**PROMPT 9 — FIDE / AICF Integration:**
> "Phase 3 mentions Swiss pairing and player rankings. Will rankings be sourced from FIDE ratings, AICF (All India Chess Federation) ratings, or maintained internally by the platform? Does the platform need to submit results to FIDE/AICF in a specific data format (e.g., FIDE tournament report)? This affects the player identity model, the results schema, and the reporting module significantly."

---

**PROMPT 10 — Regulatory & Tax Compliance:**
> "Is the platform liable to collect and remit GST on entry fees or subscription fees? At what revenue threshold does GST registration become mandatory? Does the platform need to issue GST-compliant invoices to organisers? Are there TDS obligations when disbursing collected fees to organiser accounts? These decisions affect the payment model, invoice generation, and the subscription billing architecture."

---

*End of Architecture Review*
